{{use dmy dates|date=December 2016}} {{Infobox sportsperson | name = Bjarne Eriksen | image = | fullname = | nickname = | nationality = | residence = | birth_date = {{birth date|1886|7|31|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Trondheim]], [[Norway]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1976|11|13|1886|7|31|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Oslo]], Norway | height = | weight = | website = | country = | sport = [[Fencing]] | event = }} '''Bjarne Gotfred Eriksen''' (31 July 1886 &ndash; 13 November 1976) was a Norwegian businessperson and [[fencing|fencer]].
He was born in [[Trondheim]]. He competed in the individual [[foil (fencing)|foil]] and [[épée]] events at the [[1912 Summer Olympics]].<ref name="sports-reference">{{Cite sports-reference | Bjarne Eriksen | https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/er/bjarne-eriksen-1.html | 25 August 2018 }}</ref> His brother [[Einar Eriksen (rowing)|Einar]] competed at the same Olympics in rowing.<ref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/er/einar-eriksen-1.html |title=Einar Eriksen |accessdate=25 August 2018}}</ref>
He was hired as a [[Supreme Court of Norway|Supreme Court]] barrister in 1917, but started a career in [[Norsk Hydro]] in 1926. He was originally head of the judicial and financial department, but was then promoted to Director-General (CEO) in 1941.
After the German occupation of Norway, the Germans wanted to further increase output of [[heavy water]]; the situation escalated, until Hydro's top management protested, and in early 1943, Bjarne Eriksen, the company's managing director, was arrested and sent to a concentration camp in Germany.<ref>http://www.hydro.com/en/about-hydro/Our-history/1929---1945/1943-The-Heroes-of-Telemark/</ref>
After the War, Erikson returned to his position, where he remained until 1956; after this he was chairman of the board from 1957 to 1960.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Bjarne Eriksen – norsk industrimann|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Bjarne_Eriksen/norsk_industrimann|language=Norwegian|accessdate=18 December 2009}}</ref>
