Compared to 2005, in 2013 Brazil shows a total growth of 42% with regard to exports of packaging. Especially aluminum and steel exhibit a very high overall increase in that nine-year period. In 2013 packaging made of plastics and steel were the most exported types with sales of US$268 million and US$183 million, respectively, while both combined accounted for 70% of total exports. The only packaging that was exported less in 2013 than in 2005 is wood, showing a 32% decrease from US$21 million to US$15 million. In total, US$645 million worth of packaging were exported in 2013. {| class="wikitable" |+''Exports of packaging per packaging material per year in million US$'' '''(Source: DATAMARK)''' !Packaging !2005 !2008 !2011 !2012 !2013 !% change 2005/13 |- | Plastics | align="center"|195.1 | align="center"|282.6 | align="center"|269.3 | align="center"|256.9 | align="center"|267.5 | align="center"|+37.1% |- |Wood | align="center"|21.0 | align="center"|33.3 | align="center"|20.2 | align="center"|18.8 | align="center"|14.3 | align="center"|−31.9% |- |Paper and cardboard | align="center"|90.2 | align="center"|118.1 | align="center"|119.5 | align="center"|126.4 | align="center"|123.0 | align="center"|+36.3% |- |Glass | align="center"|13.1 | align="center"|46.2 | align="center"|28.8 | align="center"|18.8 | align="center"|16.9 | align="center"|+29.0% |- |Steel | align="center"|127.6 | align="center"|251.8 | align="center"|221.7 | align="center"|212.3 | align="center"|183.4 | align="center"|+43.7% |- |Aluminum | align="center"|5.5 | align="center"|24.9 | align="center"|17.8 | align="center"|31.6 | align="center"|40.2 | align="center"|+631.0% |- |TOTAL | align="center"|452.5 | align="center"|756.9 | align="center"|677.3 | align="center"|664.8 | align="center"|645.3 | align="center"|+42.6%
|} Generally, all packaging imports have increased between 2005 and 2013. The most imported items are glass and steel packaging, exhibiting an overall increase of 560% and 384%, respectively. The imports of wood, which have increased by 30%, are the only material that shows an increase of less than 200%. All in all, Brazil imported US$1.2 billion worth of packaging in 2013. {| class="wikitable" |+''Imports of packaging per packaging material per year in million US$'' '''(Source: DATAMARK)''' !Packaging !2005 !2008 !2011 !2012 !2013 !% change 2005/13 |- |Plastics | align="center" |200.5 | align="center" |383.3 | align="center" |579.6 | align="center" |602.8 | align="center" |642.4 | align="center" | +220.4% |- |Wood | align="center" |2.0 | align="center" |2.9 | align="center" |3.2 | align="center" |2.5 | align="center" |2.6 | align="center" | +30% |- |Paper and cardboard | align="center" |59.2 | align="center" |141.5 | align="center" |245.0 | align="center" |236.0 | align="center" |252.4 | align="center" | +326.4% |- |Glass | align="center" |20.1 | align="center" |31.0 | align="center" |112.8 | align="center" |131.8 | align="center" |132.7 | align="center" | +560.2% |- |Steel | align="center" |36.2 | align="center" |89.0 | align="center" |141.1 | align="center" |159.3 | align="center" |175.5 | align="center" | +384.48% |- |Aluminum | align="center" |8.7 | align="center" |27.9 | align="center" |49.8 | align="center" |31.3 | align="center" |38.7 | align="center" | +344.8% |- |TOTAL | align="center" |326.7 | align="center" |675.6 | align="center" |1131.5 | align="center" |1163.7 | align="center" |1244.3 | align="center" | +280.9%
