The largest end use market for packaging raw materials is the beverage industry. While plastics and flexibles represent the largest share of used material for non-alcoholic beverages, alcoholic beverages heavily rely on metals (foremost aluminum) and glass. Meat and vegetables also heavily favor packaging made of plastics or flexibles. The chemical and agricultural sectors predominantly use plastics and metals due to their products requiring packaging with high durability. Low production costs are another important factor in explaining the popularity of plastics and flexibles in the Brazilian packaging sector. {| class="wikitable" |+'''End use market by value 2014 (million US$) (Source: DATAMARK)''' !Category !Product !Flexibles !Metals !Paper !Plastics !Glass !TOTAL |- | rowspan="4" |Food |Meat and vegetables | align="center"|1.284 | align="center"|625 | align="center"|401 | align="center"|2.228 | align="center"|136 | align="center"|4.675 |- |Cereals and flour based | align="center"|1.608 | align="center"|37 | align="center"|248 | align="center"|620 | align="center"| - | align="center"|2.513 |- |Sugar and chocolate | align="center"|640 | align="center"|77 | align="center"|296 | align="center"|307 | align="center"|18 | align="center"|1.339 |- |Dairy and fats | align="center"|1.290 | align="center"|261 | align="center"|53 | align="center"|965 | align="center"|77 | align="center"|2.647 |- | rowspan="2" |Drinks |Alcoholic beverages | align="center"|51 | align="center"|2.986 | align="center"|34 | align="center"|146 | align="center"|980 | align="center"|4.196 |- |Non-alcoholic beverages | align="center"|3.003 | align="center"|1.024 | align="center"|62 | align="center"|3.194 | align="center"|224 | align="center"|7.507 |- | rowspan="5" |Non-Food |Electrical and automotive | align="center"|1 | align="center"|26 | align="center"|85 | align="center"|69 | align="center"| - | align="center"|182 |- |Health and beauty | align="center"|883 | align="center"|270 | align="center"|304